  "title": "A Stray Cat Just Crashed Romeo's Death Scene",
  "script": "A cat did WHAT? In Izmir, Turkey, the Imperial Russian Ballet was performing Romeo and Juliet — climactic death scene — when a stray ginger cat wandered out. Not from backstage. Not through the wings. Just... onto the floor of the stage. It spotted Romeo lying there, dramatically lifeless, and did what cats do: laid right down next to him. Juliet is mid-grief spiral above. The audience is losing it. The dancers held character. The cat? Completely unbothered. When the curtain call came, the ginger cat got its own bow — louder applause than the leads. The venue in Izmir has a known stray problem, but none of them had ever been in a speaking role before. So: Montague, Capulet, or just a cat who had the floor?",
